5|$|Due to {{the limited}} form <b>of</b> <b>judicial</b> <b>review</b> {{available}} under the ISA, whether a person remains under detention depends largely on the Ministry of Home Affairs. This raises the question quis custodiet ipsos custodes? – who guards the guardians? If preventive detention is applied illegitimately {{in a manner that}} cripples lawful democratic opposition, the absence <b>of</b> <b>judicial</b> <b>review</b> would preclude the exposure of such abuse. It has been submitted that the voice of public opinion is most suited for this purpose.|$|E
