5000|$|While the Theodosian Code {{may seem}} to lack a {{personal}} facet due to the absence <b>of</b> <b>judicial</b> <b>reviews,</b> upon further review the legal code gives insight into Theodosius' motives behind the codification. Lenski quotes Matthews as noting that the [...] "imperial constitutions represented not only prescriptive legal formulas but also descriptive pronouncements of an emperor’s moral and ideological principles." ...|$|R
